🧠 INTUITION (SHORT & SHARP)
What are we doing?

At each index i, we can pick:

any character that appears in that column

So think:

column i → set of possible characters
What do we want?

👉 Build string with smallest period d

Meaning:

s[i] = s[i % d]
💡 Core Thought

If period = d:

Then positions:

i, i+d, i+2d, ...

👉 must have same character

🔥 So problem becomes:

For each group:

(start, start+d, start+2d...)

👉 Is there one character common in all these positions?

🧠 If YES → valid group
❌ If NO → this d is impossible
🎯 Goal

Try all d | n
👉 pick smallest valid d

⚡ HOW TO THINK IN CONTEST

“I want repeating string → try divisors → group indices → check intersection”

💻 CLEAN CODE (minimal + strong)
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define fast_io ios::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(nullptr);

int main() {
    fast_io;

    int t; cin >> t;
    while(t--) {
        int n, k;
        cin >> n >> k;

        // mp[i][c] = can we use char c at index i
        vector<vector<bool>> mp(n, vector<bool>(26, false));

        for(int i = 0; i < k; i++) {
            string s; cin >> s;
            for(int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                mp[j][s[j] - 'a'] = true;
            }
        }

        // get divisors
        vector<int> divs;
        for(int d = 1; d <= n; d++) {
            if(n % d == 0) divs.push_back(d);
        }

        string ans(n, '?');

        for(int d : divs) {

            bool ok = true;
            string temp(n, '?');

            for(int start = 0; start < d; start++) {

                bool found = false;

                // try each char
                for(int c = 0; c < 26; c++) {

                    bool valid = true;

                    // check group
                    for(int j = start; j < n; j += d) {
                        if(!mp[j][c]) {
                            valid = false;
                            break;
                        }
                    }

                    if(valid) {
                        // assign this char
                        for(int j = start; j < n; j += d) {
                            temp[j] = char('a' + c);
                        }
                        found = true;
                        break;
                    }
                }

                if(!found) {
                    ok = false;
                    break;
                }
            }

            if(ok) {
                ans = temp;
                break;
            }
        }

        cout << ans << '\n';
    }
}
🧠 FINAL MEMORY BLOCK

👉 Repeat pattern problem:

Try all d | n
Group by i % d
For each group:
find common character
If all groups valid → done
💥 ONE LINE SUMMARY

“Check smallest period where every modulo group has at least one common character.”
